## Summary

This feature allows alert messages shown on the Lesson detail page (Student Sessions section) to be configured on a per-partner basis. Specifically, the "Out of Duration Students" alert and the "Classroom Capacity" alert can be independently enabled or disabled for each partner on both Salesforce (SF) and BackOffice (BO) surfaces.

The driver for this feature is Renseikai, where a student may have multiple Lesson Allocations (LAs) for the same course (each with a different duration, due to different discount packages). This causes false-positive alerts when staff assigns the student to lessons using the longer-duration LA's class — Renseikai wants to suppress these alerts to reduce confusion.

## Acceptance Criteria

> Derived from Epic LT-96342 / LT-96343 / PBT-2608 — no formal AC numbering was present in the tickets.

**US 01 — Partner-level alert configuration**

- AC 01.1: A configuration setting allows enabling/disabling the "Out of Duration Students" alert per partner.
- AC 01.2: A configuration setting allows enabling/disabling the "Classroom Capacity" alert per partner.
- AC 01.3: The two configurations are independent; toggling one does not affect the other.

**US 02 — SF Lesson Detail Page — Out of Duration alert**

- AC 02.1: When the "Out of Duration" config is **disabled** for a partner, the alert "⚠ Lesson falls outside this student's course duration." is **hidden** on SF Lesson detail page (Student Sessions section), even when a student's lesson falls outside their LA duration.
- AC 02.2: When the "Out of Duration" config is **enabled** for a partner, the alert is **shown** on SF Lesson detail page when a student's lesson falls outside their LA duration.
- AC 02.3: When the config is disabled, the alert banner does not appear even if multiple students are out-of-duration.

**US 03 — BO Lesson Detail Page — Out of Duration alert**

- AC 03.1: When the "Out of Duration" config is **disabled** for a partner, the alert is **hidden** on BO Lesson detail page.
- AC 03.2: When the "Out of Duration" config is **enabled** for a partner, the alert is **shown** on BO Lesson detail page when applicable.

**US 04 — SF Lesson Detail Page — Classroom Capacity alert**

- AC 04.1: When the "Classroom Capacity" config is **disabled** for a partner, the alert "X/Y The number of assigned students exceeded the defined lesson capacity." is **hidden** on SF Lesson detail page, even when actual capacity is exceeded.
- AC 04.2: When the "Classroom Capacity" config is **enabled** for a partner, the alert is **shown** on SF Lesson detail page when the number of assigned students exceeds lesson capacity.

**US 05 — BO Lesson Detail Page — Classroom Capacity alert**

- AC 05.1: When the "Classroom Capacity" config is **disabled** for a partner, the alert is **hidden** on BO Lesson detail page.
- AC 05.2: When the "Classroom Capacity" config is **enabled** for a partner, the alert is **shown** on BO Lesson detail page when applicable.

**US 06 — Default behavior (regression)**

- AC 06.1: Partners with no explicit configuration continue to see both alerts as before (default behavior = both alerts shown).
- AC 06.2: Disabling alerts for one partner does not affect alert display for other partners.

